comments.author: Llama Warrior

comments.text:
+fuzzzymaine2 I'm pretty sure what he's actually saying is that, if God and 
Satan really exist (which the song never actually says anything about one 
way or the other), then God probably wouldn't care if humans did drugs 
because God made the drugs himself and gave humans the capacity to get high 
on them, possibly as a way to revitalize the soul or make spiritual 
discoveries via the altering of one's own perception. 

He goes on further to say that if he's wrong, and it turns out God really 
*doesn't* want humans to get high, then that means it is God's own fault 
for designing a system in which doing so is both possible and very 
pleasurable. 

Whatever you take away from the song depends on whether or not you believe 
in God and whether or not you believe God can make mistakes.
